# Auto Push + EC2 Deploy Workflow (Default Process)

**GitHub only stores code** (`bipulsin/trademanthan`, branch `main`). **Do not** put EC2 host, SSH keys, or deploy credentials in GitHub Actions secrets. EC2 pulls from GitHub when you tell the server to deploy.

After app-affecting changes in the local workspace `/Users/bipulsahay/TradeManthan`, unless the user says not to deploy:

1. Stage and commit relevant changes with a clear message.
2. Push to `origin main` (`git push origin main`).
3. Trigger EC2 pull + restart (server runs `backend/scripts/deploy_backend.sh`):
   - **Preferred:** `./scripts/trigger-ec2-deploy.sh` (POST `https://www.tradewithcto.com/scan/deploy-backend`)
   - **Or one step:** `./scripts/release-push-and-deploy.sh -m "commit message"`
   - **Or SSH:** `./scripts/ec2-ssh.sh 'cd /home/ubuntu/trademanthan && git pull origin main && sudo systemctl restart trademanthan-backend'` (and nginx copy if needed)

Verify via `GET https://www.tradewithcto.com/scan/deployment-status` or `./scripts/trigger-ec2-deploy.sh` log output.

Frontend is served from the same EC2 tree as the backend; one deploy updates both.

If deployment fails, surface the exact failure and next remediation step.
